==========================================================
EC2 PRACTICAL TASK 1
WEB SERVER DEPLOYMENT
==========================================================

Objective2:

Launch an EC2 instance and host a simple website.

Requirements

✓ Launch an Amazon Linux 2023 EC2 instance
✓ Create a Security Group allowing SSH and HTTP
✓ Connect using SSH
✓ Install Apache Web Server
✓ Create a custom index.html page
✓ Verify the website in a browser

Expected Output

• Apache is running
• Website is accessible using the EC2 Public IP

==========================================================
EC2 PRACTICAL TASK 2
EBS VOLUME MANAGEMENT
==========================================================

Objective

Attach an additional EBS volume to an EC2 instance.

Requirements

✓ Launch an EC2 instance
✓ Create a 5 GB EBS Volume
✓ Attach the volume to the instance
✓ Format the volume
✓ Mount it permanently using /etc/fstab
✓ Create a file inside the mounted directory

Expected Output

• Volume is mounted after reboot
• File remains available after restart

==========================================================
EC2 PRACTICAL TASK 3
AMI AND INSTANCE RECOVERY
==========================================================

Objective

Create an AMI and recover the server using it.

Requirements

✓ Launch an EC2 instance
✓ Install Apache
✓ Create a sample webpage
✓ Create an AMI
✓ Terminate the original instance
✓ Launch a new instance from the AMI

Expected Output

• New instance contains the same website
• Website opens without reconfiguration

==========================================================
EC2 PRACTICAL TASK 4
ELASTIC IP
==========================================================

Objective

Assign a static public IP to an EC2 instance.

Requirements

✓ Launch an EC2 instance
✓ Allocate an Elastic IP
✓ Associate it with the instance
✓ Verify the public IP changes to the Elastic IP
✓ Stop and Start the instance
✓ Verify the Elastic IP remains the same

Expected Output

• Instance is always accessible using the same public IP

==========================================================
EC2 PRACTICAL TASK 5
AUTO RECOVERY USING AUTO SCALING
==========================================================

Objective

Automatically replace a failed EC2 instance.

Requirements

✓ Create a Launch Template
✓ Create an Auto Scaling Group
✓ Desired Capacity = 1
✓ Minimum = 1
✓ Maximum = 2
✓ Attach the Auto Scaling Group to a Target Group
✓ Manually terminate the running EC2 instance

Expected Output

• Auto Scaling automatically launches a replacement instance
• The new instance becomes healthy in the Target Group
• Application remains available

==========================================================
BONUS CHALLENGE
==========================================================

Deploy a highly available web application using:

✓ 2 Public Subnets
✓ Application Load Balancer
✓ Launch Template
✓ Auto Scaling Group
✓ Desired Capacity = 2
✓ CPU-based Auto Scaling
✓ Health Checks

Verify:

• Load balancer distributes traffic
• Unhealthy instances are replaced automatically
• Scale out occurs when CPU > 50%
• Scale in occurs when CPU < 30%
